I was an early adopter of CamScanner and thought it was well worth the price of the license. But this app has changed their business strategy for the worse. When I first purchased the license, it was expensive compared to other apps - but it was worth it because nothing else could do what it did so well. Recently, after a hiatus from using the app, I opened it to scan a quick PDF, and it has changed...a lot... First, the license doesn't grant full access to the features like the app originally did - they have added quite a bit, but it's considered the "Pro" version now. So there is unlicensed, licensed, and licensed pro/premium. This still could be cool; but you register your account, and if you look at the "Upgrade" option, you'll see the a crossed out monthly price - I assume a discounted price or promotion. That price crossed out is $50 per month - that is outrageous. But if you're curious what the actual price is, click on the "get pro/premium" option and you'll see $50 per year, 3-days free trial, and auto bill to your Google account. So that's ~$5 per month - still not buying it though. If it's a promotion one year price that rolls auto bill after a year to $50 a month, then it's already presented me with more hassle than I want. The one-time fee for the license was fine by me, now it keeps alerting me to upgrade to premium at an insane price which, after a year, and if I forget to cancel the service, am I enrolled in an auto bill of $50 per month (or so it certainly implies)? If even one charge went through, at 13 months, I'd have over $100 in the app; but what about 14 months, $150+! No, that is outrageous - and certainly misleading. Even if the price is always ~$5/Mon, then present that price and that option. A one year fee at $50, just because it divides out to approx. ~$5 a month doesn't green light that as the advertised price. That's deceptive, and I don't trust this app on my phone anymore. I can find something just the same for little to no money for what I want. CamScanner used to be that app - a reasonable price, a great app. That's not the case anymore...

I'm updating and rewriting my review.  This is a very good app for your phone to scan documents, receipts, and anything else you need to do and convert them into .pdf format.  The auto color, b&w, etc scan adjustment is pretty darn good, however at times you may have to switch into color recognition or b&w text to get a good scan of a faded receipt.  The OCR function is pretty decent as well, probably on par with adobe OCR - wouldn't be surprised if CS uses the same recog algorithm - for use on a phone its pretty spot on if the document is clean, text dark and using a standard text font. I spent most of 1/1/17 in a hotel scanning receipts and documents for taxes.  It's safe to say I have some extensive experience with this app.  While scanning 533 different documents - CS did not crash once, nor did it give me some bizarre error.  If you save your scanned documents into google drive (as I do) make sure you upload via wifi or your cell service.  I connected to the hotel wifi, then uploaded all documents to a file in google drive.  You can use the CS free nag storage - I don't.  I use the full licensed version.

content: Its marvelous app, meets all my needs
Must have

I have been using this for work now for a good few months. I can scan and email reports to the office within a few minutes of leaving the client's house. Apart from the occasional crash (have never lost any work), it is excellent. At the price of 59p it is probably the best value software on Android.

Business Practices: Why did you take away features that early adopters paid for?  I understand that new subscribers purchase under the new subscription model, but users that paid early on?  Businesses that understand the power of user opinion understand and embrace that early users that committed to the app (via paying) should be treated differently.  They do not get "bait and switched."  Just poor business practices by IntSig.  Feature Abandonment: Why do my folders/tags disappear when I upgraded?  So now the tagging that I have done in the past is lost because IntSig wants to move to a new payment model?  Even if there is a fix, I shouldn't have to look for it.  Another really unconscionable business choice by IntSig.  Summary: I am not one for hyperbole, so read the next sentence with that in mind.  In the 5+ years that I have been an Android user, this is the worst business conduct by an app developer that I have experienced.

If you take a zoomed in picture where you can't see the whole document ( common sense ) this will crop off the edges, and the CamScanner app will have trouble cropping/undistorting it. I.e take picture far enough away to see whole page and all 4 edges.

I find this disappointing, since it should be very simple for new scans to be added to the upload queue automatically.  Also, I found that it's impossible to let the scans be uploaded to a specified folder in the cloud storage, it can only be upload to the root folder, which is not ideal. I always have a ton of pay stub receipts laying around in my car.  I know you are supposed to keep them, but usually they pile up until I end up throwing them out or losing them.  I decided to look for an app that would allow me to scan them from my phone in case I ever need to refer to one later.  Yes, I realize I should still keep the paper copy, but let's face it, that's not gonna happen.  I tried out a ton of similar apps on the market, but CamScanner worked better than all of the others that I tried.  The scans came out better, and required the least amount of tinkering after taking the photo.  I also love that I can upload them to Google Docs for safe keeping offline...  Which brings me to my feature request.  I would love to see a feature that automatically uploads the document to the cloud sources after saving it into the library.  Currently, I am not always sure if I have uploaded the file or not and have to go back and check my Google Docs account to make sure.  It would be nice to have a feature that takes care of this automatically.  Also, it would be nice to see something on the documents icon in the library showing whether the file has been uploaded or not.
